1
00:00:37,353 --> 00:00:38,980
EPISODE 6

2
00:00:46,404 --> 00:00:50,491
- Wait, that one's not expired yet.
- Oh. Right.

3
00:00:51,742 --> 00:00:53,703
It's not like you to make such a mistake.

4
00:00:54,704 --> 00:00:59,041
Did something happen yesterday
with the CCTV footage?

5
00:01:03,379 --> 00:01:06,591
Yesterday, I met Jeong Ho-myeong.

6
00:01:07,425 --> 00:01:09,426
You met Jeong Ho-myeong?

7
00:01:09,427 --> 00:01:10,470
Right.

8
00:01:11,679 --> 00:01:16,726
But that guy didn't just know me.
He knows a lot about you, too.

9
00:01:17,810 --> 00:01:19,061
Did he?

10
00:01:19,770 --> 00:01:22,064
- He said he knew me?
- Yeah.

11
00:01:22,899 --> 00:01:25,818
And not just our faces.

12
00:01:26,944 --> 00:01:29,572
He even knows why we came
to Yeongseon Island ten years ago.

13
00:01:30,323 --> 00:01:31,657
He knows everything about us.

14
00:01:37,580 --> 00:01:38,623
Okay, look.

15
00:01:39,165 --> 00:01:41,125
- There's something I need to tell you.
- Go on.

16
00:01:58,809 --> 00:02:00,353
So, what's good here?

17
00:02:00,478 --> 00:02:01,770
Best we've got are lunch boxes.

18
00:02:01,771 --> 00:02:03,522
What did you expect? Chinese food?

19
00:02:03,523 --> 00:02:04,689
What do you say?

20
00:02:04,690 --> 00:02:07,150
There's a new one.
Want me to shove it down your throat?

21
00:02:07,151 --> 00:02:08,401
Ah.

22
00:02:08,401 --> 00:02:11,154
I didn't come for a lunch box.
I came to talk.

23
00:02:11,155 --> 00:02:13,740
You threw me to the curb,
and now you want to talk?

24
00:02:13,741 --> 00:02:15,952
It's not like we're carpooling buddies,
is it?

25
00:02:16,577 --> 00:02:18,411
Cut the crap and listen up.

26
00:02:18,412 --> 00:02:21,707
I'm about to make you
an offer you can't refuse.

27
00:02:23,626 --> 00:02:26,504
I've decided to be generous.

28
00:02:28,589 --> 00:02:30,174
I'll take you in.

29
00:02:32,343 --> 00:02:33,426
What?

30
00:02:33,427 --> 00:02:36,180
Do as I say,
and I'll help you get your revenge.

31
00:02:38,349 --> 00:02:40,643
What the hell are you barking about?

32
00:02:43,062 --> 00:02:46,899
Speaking of barking,
you're pretty good at it.

33
00:02:48,568 --> 00:02:49,569
Mr. Jeong!

34
00:02:51,362 --> 00:02:52,613
How did you get that?

35
00:02:54,448 --> 00:02:57,534
Anyway, you must have realized
you can't take on Yoo In-gu alone.

36
00:02:57,535 --> 00:03:00,870
So you sought another way,
trying to meet Prosecutor Gang yesterday.

37
00:03:00,871 --> 00:03:04,457
But that route's a dead end,
so you have no options now, do you?

38
00:03:04,458 --> 00:03:06,585
You think you know everything, don't you?

39
00:03:06,586 --> 00:03:07,919
I'll never work with you!

40
00:03:07,920 --> 00:03:10,505
You'll be working for me, not with me.

41
00:03:10,506 --> 00:03:11,674
Let's just get that straight.

42
00:03:13,843 --> 00:03:17,763
I bet Gong-bok here thinks differently.

43
00:03:26,939 --> 00:03:28,940
He does have a point.

44
00:03:28,941 --> 00:03:31,360
Maybe you should think it over.

45
00:03:32,320 --> 00:03:33,321
Ma Gong-bok.

46
00:03:33,779 --> 00:03:35,822
You can't just show up out of nowhere!

47
00:03:35,823 --> 00:03:38,909
- You should have let me know!
- I just did.

48
00:03:39,368 --> 00:03:42,037
Anyway, I've said my piece.
The rest is up to you two.

49
00:03:42,038 --> 00:03:43,830
The deadline is midnight tonight.

50
00:03:43,831 --> 00:03:46,541
If you're one minute late, the deal's off.

51
00:03:46,542 --> 00:03:47,543
Choose wisely.

52
00:03:54,008 --> 00:03:55,968
- Did you betray me?
- Betray you?

53
00:03:56,469 --> 00:03:59,054
Boss,
is that all the faith you have in me?

54
00:03:59,055 --> 00:04:00,306
Mr. Jeong, huh?

55
00:04:01,140 --> 00:04:03,684
- You looked pretty chummy.
- We're not.

56
00:04:04,352 --> 00:04:05,852
I was going to tell you.

57
00:04:05,853 --> 00:04:07,688
Recently, I got to know Mr. Jeong...

58
00:04:11,442 --> 00:04:14,986
I mean, Jeong Ho-myeong
looking into Yoo In-gu.

59
00:04:14,987 --> 00:04:15,988
Yoo In-gu?

60
00:04:16,781 --> 00:04:18,324
Didn't you promise to move on?

61
00:04:22,995 --> 00:04:24,413
Boss, can you really do that?

62
00:04:26,040 --> 00:04:27,917
The betrayal ten years ago?

63
00:04:28,542 --> 00:04:30,503
And the humiliation we just suffered?

64
00:04:31,337 --> 00:04:32,755
I can't forget a single thing.

65
00:04:33,464 --> 00:04:35,423
I still hear that asshole's voice
in my sleep.

66
00:04:35,424 --> 00:04:38,468
You should have told me. I'm your boss.

67
00:04:38,469 --> 00:04:39,845
And if I had?

68
00:04:41,597 --> 00:04:44,058
Boss, do you have the guts
to give up this store?

69
00:04:48,229 --> 00:04:50,981
See? You can't give this stupid place up.

70
00:04:51,440 --> 00:04:54,067
How can you even talk about revenge?

71
00:04:54,068 --> 00:04:56,986
- Unbelievable.
- So we team up with Jeong Ho-myeong?

72
00:04:56,987 --> 00:05:00,407
And why shouldn't we?
We've been chasing Yoo and Han forever.

73
00:05:00,408 --> 00:05:02,951
We can't waste our whole lives here.

74
00:05:02,952 --> 00:05:05,578
I'd rather take action,
even if it's with Jeong Ho-myeong.

75
00:05:05,579 --> 00:05:09,291
Don't just keep saying no.
Try to be a little more open-minded.

76
00:05:10,000 --> 00:05:12,794
Just the other day,
you went after Yoo In-gu by yourself.

77
00:05:12,795 --> 00:05:14,587
- What happened then?
- What did you say?

78
00:05:14,588 --> 00:05:16,340
You're getting old.

79
00:05:18,008 --> 00:05:19,384
You can't do anything by yourself anymore.

80
00:05:19,385 --> 00:05:20,969
So you're saying I'm washed up now?

81
00:05:20,970 --> 00:05:22,722
That's not what I'm talking about!

82
00:05:23,305 --> 00:05:25,140
Just get out of here, okay?

83
00:05:25,141 --> 00:05:27,184
Go on,
run to your precious Jeong Ho-myeong!

84
00:05:55,880 --> 00:05:59,383
You're getting old.
You can't do anything by yourself anymore.

85
00:06:25,576 --> 00:06:26,619
Watch your back!

86
00:07:00,152 --> 00:07:01,612
- Here.
- Yes.

87
00:07:11,413 --> 00:07:12,998
- Hey, Chow Yunfat.
- Yes.

88
00:07:13,624 --> 00:07:16,001
The entire Bamnabi Sect
has seen your face.

89
00:07:16,752 --> 00:07:18,420
It'll be tough to work as a waiter.

90
00:07:18,921 --> 00:07:20,965
- Do you have somewhere to go?
- Well...

91
00:07:22,299 --> 00:07:26,512
Well, if it's okay with you,
I'd like to work for you.

92
00:07:29,098 --> 00:07:30,307
Work for me?

93
00:07:31,141 --> 00:07:34,103
- Why?
- Well, I...

94
00:07:35,980 --> 00:07:37,439
I want to be like you.

95
00:07:51,453 --> 00:07:52,830
1,000,000 WON

96
00:07:55,291 --> 00:07:56,584
10,000 WON

97
00:07:59,503 --> 00:08:03,048
I appreciate your help today.
But this is where we part ways.

98
00:08:03,507 --> 00:08:04,633
Take this money.

99
00:08:05,134 --> 00:08:08,386
- Be on your way.
- Where would I even go?

100
00:08:08,387 --> 00:08:09,638
You want to be like me?

101
00:08:10,347 --> 00:08:11,931
And for what?

102
00:08:11,932 --> 00:08:13,934
You'd be a thug
who only knows how to fight.

103
00:08:14,727 --> 00:08:17,521
Don't get any crazy ideas. Start fresh.

104
00:08:27,948 --> 00:08:29,575
Chow

105
00:08:30,451 --> 00:08:31,911
After Chow Yun Fat...

106
00:08:32,410 --> 00:08:36,205
You're the first man
I've ever wanted to be like!

107
00:08:36,206 --> 00:08:38,332
It's not that I have some kind of fantasy.

108
00:08:38,333 --> 00:08:42,796
No matter where you go,
I want to follow you!

109
00:08:43,547 --> 00:08:45,883
And I want to be more like you!

110
00:08:46,800 --> 00:08:48,886
Please, take me in!

111
00:09:23,671 --> 00:09:25,381
Prosecutor Gang, you're coming with us.

112
00:09:39,478 --> 00:09:40,771
Those bastards.

113
00:09:42,189 --> 00:09:44,191
Okay, fine.

114
00:09:45,442 --> 00:09:47,653
So you want to take this all the way, huh?

115
00:09:48,988 --> 00:09:50,990
Yes, come in.

116
00:09:51,991 --> 00:09:54,910
So, our members would like to see you.

117
00:09:55,744 --> 00:09:58,163
- Members?
- The people from the shelter.

118
00:09:59,915 --> 00:10:02,751
I know it's late,
but thank you for saving me.

119
00:10:03,293 --> 00:10:05,795
Look, I don't need your gratitude.

120
00:10:05,796 --> 00:10:07,047
But I have a question.

121
00:10:08,382 --> 00:10:10,050
Why were you in the sea water?

122
00:10:10,634 --> 00:10:12,553
- Are you really a prosecutor?
- Hey!

123
00:10:13,137 --> 00:10:15,096
- I'm sorry.
- What? I'm curious.

124
00:10:15,097 --> 00:10:18,975
She had a prosecutor's ID,
but told us not to report anything.

125
00:10:18,976 --> 00:10:21,979
Is this going to be on the news?
We deserve to know.

126
00:10:25,899 --> 00:10:28,235
I was investigating a violent crime.

127
00:10:28,736 --> 00:10:31,196
I had an accident
during the investigation.

128
00:10:32,156 --> 00:10:34,615
And if my location is exposed,
it could be bad.

129
00:10:34,616 --> 00:10:37,076
It could seriously jeopardize
the whole investigation.

130
00:10:37,077 --> 00:10:39,204
I know this is a huge favor to ask.

131
00:10:39,329 --> 00:10:44,167
But could I stay here in secret
just for a short while?

132
00:10:44,168 --> 00:10:46,294
Oh, of course.

133
00:10:46,295 --> 00:10:49,047
So it's like a stakeout.
A sting operation.

134
00:10:49,048 --> 00:10:50,632
That's what it is.

135
00:10:51,133 --> 00:10:52,509
I'm a cop, so I get it.

136
00:10:53,719 --> 00:10:56,054
But are you sure you'll be okay here?

137
00:10:56,055 --> 00:11:00,808
Oh, yes, of course.
Mr. Bong told me what you all do here.

138
00:11:00,809 --> 00:11:04,854
You help victims who lost their property
by Heaven Capital.

139
00:11:04,855 --> 00:11:06,731
You take in people
with nowhere else to go.

140
00:11:06,732 --> 00:11:09,901
You're such wonderful people.
Of course I can trust you.

141
00:11:09,902 --> 00:11:11,069
Oh, please.

142
00:11:11,070 --> 00:11:14,697
We helped out some neighbors.
It's really nothing great.

143
00:11:14,698 --> 00:11:16,742
So, speaking of.

144
00:11:17,326 --> 00:11:20,578
I heard you've collected some materials
related to Heaven Capital here.

145
00:11:20,579 --> 00:11:24,040
May I look through them?

146
00:11:24,041 --> 00:11:26,292
I mean, that bastard Yoo In-gu...

147
00:11:26,293 --> 00:11:29,296
No, that's not what I mean.
This is about Heaven Capital.

148
00:11:29,421 --> 00:11:32,340
I'd like to see what illegal activities
they've been up to.

149
00:11:32,341 --> 00:11:34,550
I believe I can research things like that.

150
00:11:34,551 --> 00:11:37,303
You just woke up.
Aren't you pushing yourself?

151
00:11:37,304 --> 00:11:39,847
What's there to worry about?
You're here for her.

152
00:11:39,848 --> 00:11:41,557
- Excuse me?
- Just stick with her.

153
00:11:41,558 --> 00:11:44,227
Make sure she doesn't
have to lift a finger.

154
00:11:44,228 --> 00:11:45,353
But I'm tired.

155
00:11:45,354 --> 00:11:46,437
No, it's okay.

156
00:11:46,438 --> 00:11:49,148
I'd just like to look over the materials.

157
00:11:49,149 --> 00:11:51,192
No, no. You still have
trouble getting around.

158
00:11:51,193 --> 00:11:53,694
Je-sun can help you out a little longer.

159
00:11:53,695 --> 00:11:54,780
Yeah.

160
00:11:56,615 --> 00:11:58,450
I pulled an all-nighter yesterday.

161
00:12:13,966 --> 00:12:16,218
TEMPORARILY CLOSED. WE'LL BE BACK SOON.

162
00:12:18,345 --> 00:12:19,346
Hey.

163
00:12:31,316 --> 00:12:32,484
Can you handle it?

164
00:12:33,485 --> 00:12:34,486
Sir?

165
00:12:35,028 --> 00:12:36,780
Rebuilding Hwasan after a decade.

166
00:12:37,865 --> 00:12:40,826
Are you confident you can take down
the Ingu Sect and Han Gyeong-wook?

167
00:12:45,080 --> 00:12:46,081
Boss.

168
00:12:46,915 --> 00:12:49,459
I've gotten rusty
after taking ten years off.

169
00:12:50,878 --> 00:12:54,172
So if you're going to whine
about me getting old...

170
00:12:54,173 --> 00:12:55,841
I'll just leave you here right now.

171
00:13:05,184 --> 00:13:06,767
I'd never do that!

172
00:13:06,768 --> 00:13:09,937
I've waited ten years for this day.

173
00:13:09,938 --> 00:13:11,106
I will do my best.

174
00:13:11,648 --> 00:13:15,152
Tell me everything that happened with
Yoo In-gu and Jeong Ho-myeong.

175
00:13:15,861 --> 00:13:17,279
And don't hide anything from me.

176
00:13:18,030 --> 00:13:19,531
And whatever we do,
we see it through together.

177
00:13:20,407 --> 00:13:23,701
- Yes, boss.
- And...

178
00:13:23,702 --> 00:13:26,705
Gong-bok, you were right.
I really have gotten old.

179
00:13:29,291 --> 00:13:32,127
- I don't think that's what I meant.
- No, it's true.

180
00:13:32,836 --> 00:13:35,797
I'm no match for the Ingu Sect on my own.

181
00:13:37,424 --> 00:13:39,092
Contact Jeong Ho-myeong and talk to him.

182
00:13:39,676 --> 00:13:42,054
- Tell him I want to see him now.
- Yes, sir.

183
00:13:47,809 --> 00:13:50,144
Hey, Mr. Yoo.

184
00:13:50,145 --> 00:13:52,439
Oh? You look happy. You're looking good.

185
00:13:52,981 --> 00:13:56,652
- So? Did everything work out?
- I took care of everything.

186
00:13:57,110 --> 00:14:00,113
Wow, for real? So fast, Mr. Yoo.

187
00:14:00,572 --> 00:14:03,825
So, what's your method?
You have to tell me your secret.

188
00:14:04,660 --> 00:14:07,579
It's something you could never pull off.
Don't get cute.

189
00:14:08,205 --> 00:14:10,499
Watch your mouth in front of Chief Han.
Got it?

190
00:14:11,416 --> 00:14:15,670
- Okay, got it.
- Here are the Imcheon mayoral polls.

191
00:14:15,671 --> 00:14:17,755
Between Kim Seon-jung
and Han Gyeong-wook...

192
00:14:17,756 --> 00:14:20,758
- I'm here.
- A two-way race has emerged.

193
00:14:20,759 --> 00:14:21,842
What are you doing?

194
00:14:21,843 --> 00:14:24,762
- A two-point gap.
- I see you're watching TV.

195
00:14:24,763 --> 00:14:28,474
Candidate Kim Seon-jung's strength
lies in his deep roots in Imcheon.

196
00:14:28,475 --> 00:14:31,560
He has established an image
as an incorruptible educator.

197
00:14:31,561 --> 00:14:36,108
He has become a rival to Han Gyeong-wook
in Imcheon's conservative stronghold.

198
00:14:36,233 --> 00:14:38,402
His approval ratings
have recently been soaring...

199
00:14:42,197 --> 00:14:44,783
You're keeping a close eye on the news.

200
00:14:45,659 --> 00:14:48,453
What's the point of watching the news?
It's all a bunch of nonsense.

201
00:14:49,413 --> 00:14:50,496
A bunch of nonsense?

202
00:14:50,497 --> 00:14:53,834
They can run their mouths all day,
but for our Yeongseon Island Project...

203
00:14:54,626 --> 00:14:57,838
You would have to
win this election, right?

204
00:14:58,755 --> 00:15:00,256
Chairman Do, your thoughts?

205
00:15:00,257 --> 00:15:03,968
Well, I have no doubt you will win.

206
00:15:03,969 --> 00:15:05,262
But that kind of bad news...

207
00:15:06,555 --> 00:15:08,306
Oh, I'm sorry. I just think...

208
00:15:08,307 --> 00:15:11,768
It's best to nip
these negative stories in the bud.

209
00:15:13,937 --> 00:15:17,064
Now you're talking, Mr. Do.

210
00:15:17,065 --> 00:15:19,108
Nipping things in the bud
is my specialty, isn't it?

211
00:15:19,109 --> 00:15:21,819
Kidnapping, blackmail...
Just say the word.

212
00:15:21,820 --> 00:15:23,030
Mr. Yoo.

213
00:15:24,031 --> 00:15:26,533
Can't you see I'm talking
to Mr. Do right now?

214
00:15:27,284 --> 00:15:29,536
Why do you keep spouting nonsense?

215
00:15:30,078 --> 00:15:31,371
I'm sorry.

216
00:15:32,414 --> 00:15:33,664
Go on, Mr. Do.

217
00:15:33,665 --> 00:15:37,419
Yes, an election is ultimately
a battle of images, isn't it?

218
00:15:38,211 --> 00:15:40,463
He's cultivated one
as an incorruptible educator.

219
00:15:40,464 --> 00:15:43,382
- So let's turn him into corrupt trash.
- How long will it take?

220
00:15:43,383 --> 00:15:45,802
A week? A week will be more than enough.

221
00:15:48,889 --> 00:15:49,973
Mr. Yoo.

222
00:15:50,807 --> 00:15:54,061
You'll support him.
Make sure it moves quickly.

223
00:15:54,186 --> 00:15:57,396
You want me to wipe his ass?

224
00:15:57,397 --> 00:15:58,774
I'm a busy man.

225
00:16:00,901 --> 00:16:05,739
I thought your company ran itself,
but you're busy?

226
00:16:06,573 --> 00:16:09,534
What? You got a side hustle
I don't know about?

227
00:16:11,495 --> 00:16:14,373
No, sir. I spoke out of turn.

228
00:16:15,916 --> 00:16:18,126
And just so we're clear.

229
00:16:18,960 --> 00:16:21,588
If anything goes wrong with this project

230
00:16:22,756 --> 00:16:25,300
all of you will be held responsible.

231
00:16:27,135 --> 00:16:29,971
- Do I make myself clear?
- Yes, sir. Understood.

232
00:16:49,366 --> 00:16:51,910
There's so much to do.
This is a real headache.

233
00:16:55,580 --> 00:16:56,789
Oh, Mr. Nam.

234
00:16:56,790 --> 00:16:58,582
Did you get
all the files from Secretary Baek?

235
00:16:58,583 --> 00:17:02,336
Yes. I received the files
on Kim Seon-jung.

236
00:17:02,337 --> 00:17:04,297
Give those files to Geum Kang-sik.

237
00:17:05,799 --> 00:17:09,135
Hey, Mr. Yoo, don't worry about this.
We'll take care of it.

238
00:17:09,136 --> 00:17:10,971
Hey, you think I want to work with you?

239
00:17:11,096 --> 00:17:12,597
With me?

240
00:17:13,598 --> 00:17:15,684
Weren't you told to support me?

241
00:17:16,143 --> 00:17:19,855
It's just that
I don't really need your support.

242
00:17:21,021 --> 00:17:23,983
This job doesn't call for
your brutish methods.

243
00:17:24,693 --> 00:17:27,319
What? Brutish? You son of a bitch.

244
00:17:30,240 --> 00:17:31,407
- Hey, Kang-sik.
- Yes, sir.

245
00:17:31,408 --> 00:17:33,994
Tomorrow, take the guys
and look into Kim Seon-jung.

246
00:17:34,119 --> 00:17:37,080
Sir? But Chairman Do just said
there was no need...

247
00:17:41,460 --> 00:17:42,752
Did you just dodge?

248
00:17:43,503 --> 00:17:46,006
Hey, did you take money
from that bastard or something?

249
00:17:46,840 --> 00:17:48,632
Do his words come before mine?

250
00:17:48,633 --> 00:17:49,634
No, sir.

251
00:17:50,469 --> 00:17:53,889
Kidnapping, blackmail, false imprisonment.

252
00:17:54,431 --> 00:17:57,933
Find anything on Kim Seon-jung
we can use as leverage.

253
00:17:57,934 --> 00:17:59,311
Don't come back empty-handed.

254
00:17:59,811 --> 00:18:01,771
- Got it?
- Yes, sir.

255
00:18:08,320 --> 00:18:09,613
Here's my decision.

256
00:18:10,780 --> 00:18:13,532
I'll accept your offer. On one condition.

257
00:18:13,533 --> 00:18:15,410
Don't even think about giving me orders.

258
00:18:16,161 --> 00:18:19,289
We're working together for a short time
to get what we both want.

259
00:18:19,956 --> 00:18:21,583
I have no intention of becoming your pawn.

260
00:18:24,294 --> 00:18:26,755
So you're determined
to hold on to your pride.

261
00:18:30,717 --> 00:18:32,384
Look here, you thug.

262
00:18:32,385 --> 00:18:35,889
What happens if you go rogue
and ruin the whole operation?

263
00:18:37,390 --> 00:18:40,268
- You want a piece of this thug?
- Boss, calm down. Please.

264
00:18:40,852 --> 00:18:44,271
Does he have a solid plan to take down
Yoo In-gu and Han Gyeong-wook?

265
00:18:44,272 --> 00:18:46,107
Or is he just trying to use us?

266
00:18:46,233 --> 00:18:51,070
Do you know what Yoo In-gu's doing,
or what Han Gyeong-wook is up to?

267
00:18:51,071 --> 00:18:54,615
- You don't have a clue, do you?
- Well...

268
00:18:54,616 --> 00:18:57,159
Ten years of scanning barcodes
has dulled your edge.

269
00:18:57,160 --> 00:18:59,912
Just follow my orders,
not question everything.

270
00:18:59,913 --> 00:19:02,415
Well, you spent ten years
working in a Chinese kitchen.

271
00:19:02,958 --> 00:19:05,960
Special agent, my ass.
When did you last wear a suit?

272
00:19:05,961 --> 00:19:07,545
Who's calling who washed up?

273
00:19:07,546 --> 00:19:09,339
You want to be the boss?
Let's settle this!

274
00:19:10,882 --> 00:19:12,716
Once a thug, always a thug.

275
00:19:12,717 --> 00:19:14,635
Think I can't take you? Huh?

276
00:19:14,636 --> 00:19:16,303
Don't you remember ten years ago?

277
00:19:16,304 --> 00:19:19,515
- Come on, this isn't why we met.
- Get out of my way!

278
00:19:19,516 --> 00:19:20,933
No, get out of the way.

279
00:19:20,934 --> 00:19:22,518
Of course I remember ten years ago.

280
00:19:22,519 --> 00:19:24,270
If it hadn't rained that day

281
00:19:24,271 --> 00:19:26,981
- I would've finished you for good!
- Wow, really?

282
00:19:26,982 --> 00:19:29,942
You're even dumber than you look.
Want me to give you a reminder?

283
00:19:29,943 --> 00:19:31,527
- Move!
- Get out of my way!

284
00:19:31,528 --> 00:19:32,653
- Go on, you bastard!
- Boss!

285
00:19:32,654 --> 00:19:34,154
- I said get out of my way!
- Boss!

286
00:19:34,155 --> 00:19:36,407
- Move, you punk!
- Bring it!

287
00:19:36,408 --> 00:19:39,159
- I'll teach him a lesson!
- Mr. Jeong!

288
00:19:39,160 --> 00:19:41,120
- Boss!
- Move!

289
00:19:41,121 --> 00:19:42,371
You're getting a call. Answer it!

290
00:19:42,372 --> 00:19:44,456
Get out of my way!

291
00:19:44,457 --> 00:19:47,168
- I'll teach him a lesson.
- Answer your phone!

292
00:19:48,295 --> 00:19:49,462
You're getting a call!

293
00:19:56,845 --> 00:19:57,846
JO SEONG-WON

294
00:19:58,680 --> 00:20:01,016
- Yeah?
- Hey, Prosecutor Gang's alive.

295
00:20:01,558 --> 00:20:04,143
- Really?
- I don't know where she went yet.

296
00:20:04,144 --> 00:20:05,644
But I think she washed ashore.

297
00:20:05,645 --> 00:20:07,939
How's your end?
Any progress with Gang Beom-ryong?

298
00:20:09,065 --> 00:20:11,860
- What are you looking at?
- I'm working on it. I'll call you back.

299
00:20:13,320 --> 00:20:15,530
- Move!
- Come on!

300
00:20:27,208 --> 00:20:28,584
Gang is alive.

301
00:20:28,585 --> 00:20:30,586
- For real?
- Of course. Damn it.

302
00:20:30,587 --> 00:20:33,465
Boss, that means
we don't have to do this, right?

303
00:20:34,633 --> 00:20:37,844
Mr. Jeong, do you want to
waste your energy fighting him?

304
00:20:39,763 --> 00:20:43,058
All right, fine. Have it your way.
A temporary alliance it is.

305
00:20:43,642 --> 00:20:45,517
We know Gang is alive now.

306
00:20:45,518 --> 00:20:47,896
- We can't waste time.
- Then let's be clear.

307
00:20:48,730 --> 00:20:49,813
We don't work for you.

308
00:20:49,814 --> 00:20:52,900
Jeez, I get it.
Call it whatever you want, I don't care.

309
00:20:52,901 --> 00:20:55,153
But don't question my operation again.

310
00:20:55,779 --> 00:20:59,115
- Or this alliance is over. Got it?
- Fine!

311
00:21:02,410 --> 00:21:04,371
JEONGSEOK SINGLE ROOMS

312
00:21:06,706 --> 00:21:11,585
Most of the victims were people
who gambled at Heaven Casino.

313
00:21:11,586 --> 00:21:15,339
They lured in ordinary residents
and got them into gambling debt.

314
00:21:15,340 --> 00:21:18,050
And then they intentionally confiscated
their homes and land.

315
00:21:18,051 --> 00:21:19,344
But it's strange.

316
00:21:25,308 --> 00:21:29,019
On Yeongseon Island, they only took land
from Nakwon-ri residents.

317
00:21:29,020 --> 00:21:30,104
NAKWON-RI

318
00:21:30,105 --> 00:21:31,147
But why?

319
00:21:31,856 --> 00:21:35,859
Properties in a small village
are a hassle to sell.

320
00:21:35,860 --> 00:21:38,738
Even with development plans,
it'd take a long time to profit.

321
00:21:40,365 --> 00:21:43,827
Yoo In-gu is definitely acting
on Han Gyeong-wook's orders.

322
00:21:44,285 --> 00:21:46,830
So why would Han Gyeong-wook
give such an order?

323
00:21:48,164 --> 00:21:52,710
- They're using Yeongseon Island to...
- Here's your meal.

324
00:21:52,711 --> 00:21:53,712
Oh, thanks.

325
00:21:57,674 --> 00:21:58,967
Come in.

326
00:22:00,510 --> 00:22:01,885
Here you go.

327
00:22:01,886 --> 00:22:04,304
Oh, thank you. Just leave it there.
I'll eat in a bit.

328
00:22:04,305 --> 00:22:06,014
Oh, okay.

329
00:22:06,015 --> 00:22:08,768
Hey, can I ask you something?

330
00:22:10,520 --> 00:22:13,772
Do you think there's a way
for the victims to get their homes back?

331
00:22:13,773 --> 00:22:15,942
Well, I'm not sure yet.

332
00:22:17,861 --> 00:22:19,153
You should eat something first.

333
00:22:19,154 --> 00:22:21,489
Yes, if you just leave it,
I'll eat it. Thank you.

334
00:22:21,614 --> 00:22:24,241
You have to eat before it gets cold.
And take your medicine.

335
00:22:24,242 --> 00:22:26,953
Just a moment. There we go.

336
00:22:35,712 --> 00:22:37,505
Say ah.

337
00:22:39,591 --> 00:22:41,550
- Can I do it myself?
- Of course.

338
00:22:41,551 --> 00:22:43,595
Thank you.

339
00:22:43,720 --> 00:22:46,639
After you finish the porridge,
make sure you take your meds.

340
00:22:48,183 --> 00:22:51,936
If you get seawater in your ear,
you can get a nasty ear infection.

341
00:22:55,398 --> 00:22:58,150
- Are you a nurse, by any chance?
- Huh?

342
00:22:58,151 --> 00:23:00,403
It's just,
you seem to be a natural at this.

343
00:23:01,404 --> 00:23:04,324
I fell into the ocean ten years ago,
just like you.

344
00:23:04,449 --> 00:23:08,076
I'm just doing for you
what the person who saved me did.

345
00:23:08,077 --> 00:23:10,662
- Why did you fall in?
- I have no idea.

346
00:23:10,663 --> 00:23:11,997
What?

347
00:23:11,998 --> 00:23:15,083
Oh, there's no water.
I'll get you some warm water.

348
00:23:15,084 --> 00:23:17,212
Eat up before it gets cold.

349
00:23:17,879 --> 00:23:19,756
So busy today.

350
00:23:23,051 --> 00:23:27,346
Ah, to meet the two men
who once ruled the Hwasan Sect.

351
00:23:27,347 --> 00:23:30,432
- It's an honor to meet you.
- The honor is all mine.

352
00:23:30,433 --> 00:23:32,644
Why are you being so formal
with these thugs?

353
00:23:33,978 --> 00:23:37,272
We may not have started off
on the right foot.

354
00:23:37,273 --> 00:23:39,107
But let's put the past behind us...

355
00:23:39,108 --> 00:23:42,237
- and focus on what's ahead.
- Yes, I'll do my absolute best.

356
00:23:43,029 --> 00:23:45,865
But is Prosecutor Gang really alive?

357
00:23:45,990 --> 00:23:48,242
Yes, we're certain she's alive.

358
00:23:48,243 --> 00:23:50,495
It'll take some time
to pinpoint her location.

359
00:23:51,120 --> 00:23:54,414
But before that,
there's something I need you two to do.

360
00:23:54,415 --> 00:23:57,377
Not Ma Gong-bok.
I need him to keep tabs on Bulgae.

361
00:23:58,253 --> 00:24:01,548
Hey, so about Bulgae.

362
00:24:02,090 --> 00:24:04,508
He was chased by the Heaven Capital guys
and got away.

363
00:24:04,509 --> 00:24:06,844
- So you lost him?
- We're looking. We'll find him.

364
00:24:06,845 --> 00:24:08,346
Are you kidding me?

365
00:24:09,681 --> 00:24:10,806
Hey.

366
00:24:10,807 --> 00:24:12,850
It's not like you weren't distracted
with other things yourself.

367
00:24:12,851 --> 00:24:14,351
You two are a real piece of work.

368
00:24:14,352 --> 00:24:15,686
Relax.

369
00:24:15,687 --> 00:24:17,981
There's something more urgent
than finding this Bulgae.

370
00:24:19,232 --> 00:24:22,360
Remember what Yoo In-gu said
when we bugged him?

371
00:24:23,528 --> 00:24:24,611
- The drug deal.
- What?

372
00:24:24,612 --> 00:24:25,696
- What?
- What?

373
00:24:25,697 --> 00:24:27,573
That bastard Yoo In-gu is dealing drugs?

374
00:24:27,574 --> 00:24:29,908
He said soon,
they'd be making a huge deal.

375
00:24:29,909 --> 00:24:34,037
One that will decide their fate.
The question is, how do we stop them?

376
00:24:34,038 --> 00:24:37,457
Wait a minute.
Can the four of us stop that?

377
00:24:37,458 --> 00:24:38,876
I mean, I hate to admit it.

378
00:24:38,877 --> 00:24:43,338
But the Ingu Sect is way too big
for just the four of us to take on.

379
00:24:43,339 --> 00:24:46,508
Since we're doing this anyway,
let's just go straight for the top.

380
00:24:46,509 --> 00:24:49,928
Do you think Yoo In-gu or Han Gyeong-wook
will even bat an eye over one deal?

381
00:24:49,929 --> 00:24:52,764
Typical thug mindset.
You only see what's in front of you.

382
00:24:52,765 --> 00:24:54,725
- What?
- You take out the boss, then what?

383
00:24:54,726 --> 00:24:56,643
You just bury him?

384
00:24:56,644 --> 00:24:57,728
And Gang Beom-ryong,

385
00:24:57,729 --> 00:25:00,273
did you forget what happened
when you charged in alone?

386
00:25:01,441 --> 00:25:04,943
Those bastards have built a fortress.

387
00:25:04,944 --> 00:25:06,403
You want to tear it down?

388
00:25:06,404 --> 00:25:08,823
You have to take it down step by step.

389
00:25:09,657 --> 00:25:13,661
Our priority is to stop the drug deal
and land a critical blow.

390
00:25:13,786 --> 00:25:16,080
So you have a plan?

391
00:25:19,125 --> 00:25:20,418
First, Ma Gong-bok.

392
00:25:21,586 --> 00:25:25,590
Put your search for Bulgae on hold,
and start looking into Yoo In-gu.

393
00:25:26,299 --> 00:25:28,593
Don't miss a single thing they do.

394
00:25:29,427 --> 00:25:31,887
- Yes, sir.
- Hey, Ho-myeong.

395
00:25:31,888 --> 00:25:34,389
Tailing, wiretapping...
This isn't child's play.

396
00:25:34,390 --> 00:25:35,849
You sure a civilian can handle it?

397
00:25:35,850 --> 00:25:37,225
He's not just a civilian.

398
00:25:37,226 --> 00:25:41,314
He stalked me, an elite agent,
for ten whole years.

399
00:25:42,815 --> 00:25:44,608
Well, I don't mean to brag.

400
00:25:44,609 --> 00:25:47,527
But I know his anniversary,
Ji-woo's birthday

401
00:25:47,528 --> 00:25:49,404
and how many spoons he owns.

402
00:25:49,405 --> 00:25:53,159
Just let me know if you ever need to
tail someone and gather intel.

403
00:25:54,035 --> 00:25:55,118
Nice.

404
00:25:55,119 --> 00:25:57,914
See? Now you get
how creepy and relentless he is.

405
00:25:59,999 --> 00:26:03,543
And you, with your leg,
don't even think about overdoing it.

406
00:26:03,544 --> 00:26:06,713
Go through the police CCTV footage
he has access to.

407
00:26:06,714 --> 00:26:09,592
- Track Prosecutor Gang.
- Okay, got it.

408
00:26:13,972 --> 00:26:16,975
What? What do you want from me?

409
00:26:17,976 --> 00:26:20,560
- You just get ready.
- I'm already ready. Ready for what?

410
00:26:20,561 --> 00:26:21,604
To run like a dog.

411
00:26:29,904 --> 00:26:31,154
Try not to wreck the car.

412
00:26:31,155 --> 00:26:34,074
I haven't forgotten
about that scratch on the door.

413
00:26:34,075 --> 00:26:36,035
Jeez, I know. I'll be careful.

414
00:26:38,913 --> 00:26:40,372
Thank you.

415
00:26:40,373 --> 00:26:43,041
I saw the dent in the back too!

416
00:26:43,042 --> 00:26:47,130
I told you that wasn't me.
For goodness' sake.

417
00:26:52,677 --> 00:26:55,054
I'll be on my way. See you in the evening.

418
00:26:55,179 --> 00:26:56,931
- Say hi to Seon-jung for me.
- Okay.

419
00:27:34,052 --> 00:27:35,844
- Oh, dear.
- Oh, hey.

420
00:27:35,845 --> 00:27:37,555
- Welcome.
- Hey, O-ran!

421
00:27:39,682 --> 00:27:40,807
- Boss.
- Yeah.

422
00:27:40,808 --> 00:27:42,769
A woman just went into
Kim Seon-jung's house.

423
00:27:43,686 --> 00:27:44,854
Get a picture.

424
00:27:47,440 --> 00:27:48,524
Did you get it?

425
00:27:51,944 --> 00:27:54,405
But boss, seriously,
isn't this a bit much?

426
00:27:54,530 --> 00:27:56,865
We're already swamped with the drug deal.

427
00:27:56,866 --> 00:28:00,203
Plus the Martial Arts Master,
and now Kim Seon-jung, too?

428
00:28:00,870 --> 00:28:03,498
The guys are complaining,
saying it's too much work.

429
00:28:03,623 --> 00:28:06,125
If you don't use your brain,
your body pays the price.

430
00:28:07,752 --> 00:28:11,589
If you and I want to save our own skin,
we better do whatever we can.

431
00:28:11,964 --> 00:28:14,717
We must get new intel
on Kim Seon-jung before Jo does.

432
00:28:16,344 --> 00:28:18,888
- But for how long?
- Suck it up a little longer, you punk!

433
00:28:22,308 --> 00:28:25,019
This will all be over soon.

434
00:28:27,939 --> 00:28:30,233
All right. Look here.

435
00:28:33,319 --> 00:28:34,862
- See? This is rice...
- Yes.

436
00:28:35,530 --> 00:28:38,865
Underneath are beans, barley, potatoes,
and sweet potatoes.

437
00:28:38,866 --> 00:28:41,202
I was going to donate this
to a homeless shelter.

438
00:28:41,994 --> 00:28:44,455
But you all need it more right now,
so take it.

439
00:28:45,081 --> 00:28:46,790
I'm so sorry.

440
00:28:46,791 --> 00:28:49,876
- I'm sorry for always whining.
- How are the victims?

441
00:28:49,877 --> 00:28:52,964
- Is the number still increasing?
- Yes.

442
00:28:53,881 --> 00:28:58,093
We're gathering all the evidence,
but Heaven Capital must've pulled strings.

443
00:28:58,094 --> 00:29:01,096
Police and lawyers keep saying
nothing illegal occurred.

444
00:29:01,097 --> 00:29:04,684
Even reporters don't care,
saying it's not newsworthy.

445
00:29:05,393 --> 00:29:09,688
- I don't know what I should do now.
- Damn it. Just hold on a little longer.

446
00:29:09,689 --> 00:29:12,107
Wait until I get elected.

447
00:29:12,108 --> 00:29:15,152
The first thing I'll do is
create a relief plan for the victims.

448
00:29:15,153 --> 00:29:19,364
- How ambitious.
- I'm number one in the polls, kid.

449
00:29:19,365 --> 00:29:20,866
I know.

450
00:29:20,867 --> 00:29:23,911
That's why you need to get elected soon.

451
00:29:24,579 --> 00:29:27,247
At this rate, everyone on
Yeongseon Island will be ruined.

452
00:29:27,248 --> 00:29:29,541
Let's just hang in there
a little longer, huh?

453
00:29:29,542 --> 00:29:31,209
Okay.

454
00:29:31,210 --> 00:29:33,337
- Hand me that one.
- Here.

455
00:29:36,215 --> 00:29:39,926
- We'll put this to good use, sir.
- Let me know if you need more.

456
00:29:39,927 --> 00:29:41,888
- Thank you.
- You should get going.

457
00:29:42,638 --> 00:29:44,182
- I'll see you later.
- Okay then.

458
00:29:48,895 --> 00:29:49,896
Huh?

459
00:29:50,563 --> 00:29:51,564
She's driving away.

460
00:29:52,481 --> 00:29:54,692
- What do we do?
- Obviously, we follow her.

461
00:29:59,655 --> 00:30:02,074
Wait, who's that?
I feel like I've seen her before.

462
00:30:47,703 --> 00:30:48,746
Switch.

463
00:30:56,671 --> 00:30:59,130
Damn it. She's onto us.

464
00:30:59,131 --> 00:31:00,841
I told you to keep some distance.

465
00:31:24,115 --> 00:31:26,409
- Perfect. Now get right on her tail.
- Yes, sir.

466
00:31:55,980 --> 00:31:58,190
It's a dead end.

467
00:31:58,316 --> 00:31:59,649
- Right.
- Hey, get ready.

468
00:31:59,650 --> 00:32:01,319
- Right.
- Kill the engine.

469
00:33:14,934 --> 00:33:15,935
IMCHEON 30 BA 8690

470
00:33:18,437 --> 00:33:24,443
ORAN CHINESE RESTAURANT

471
00:33:27,238 --> 00:33:28,239
Cuckoo!

472
00:33:32,743 --> 00:33:33,827
Cuckoo!

473
00:33:33,828 --> 00:33:36,663
- Ji-woo.
- Daddy! It's Daddy!

474
00:33:36,664 --> 00:33:40,792
- Ji-woo. Hey there. Have you been well?
- Uh-huh.

475
00:33:40,793 --> 00:33:43,461
- Have you eaten today?
- Daddy, I missed you.

476
00:33:43,462 --> 00:33:46,047
I missed you too.

477
00:33:46,048 --> 00:33:48,092
What's with the dramatic family reunion?

478
00:33:50,719 --> 00:33:52,012
Hey, Jeong.

479
00:33:53,764 --> 00:33:56,683
Whoa, you scared me.
What brings you out so early?

480
00:33:56,684 --> 00:33:57,768
Where have you been?

481
00:33:58,436 --> 00:33:59,686
Do you know how worried we've been?

482
00:33:59,687 --> 00:34:01,021
Ever since you left

483
00:34:01,897 --> 00:34:04,649
the two of us have had it so rough,
you have no idea.

484
00:34:04,650 --> 00:34:08,695
O-ran is always out and about
with her K-pop obsession.

485
00:34:08,696 --> 00:34:13,783
At this rate,
we're going to work ourselves to death.

486
00:34:13,784 --> 00:34:15,201
You're back for good, right?

487
00:34:15,202 --> 00:34:16,495
You're not leaving again, are you?

488
00:34:17,913 --> 00:34:20,331
Daddy? Are you back for good?

489
00:34:21,876 --> 00:34:25,379
I just stopped by for a bit today
to see Ji-woo.

490
00:34:27,547 --> 00:34:30,467
When on earth are you going to
make up with O-ran, huh?

491
00:34:30,467 --> 00:34:33,178
She blocked my number,
so there's nothing I can do.

492
00:34:33,179 --> 00:34:36,181
- A letter. You could write her a letter.
- She'd just tear it up.

493
00:34:36,181 --> 00:34:39,601
So you're just going to do nothing?
You're not going to come back?

494
00:34:39,601 --> 00:34:43,521
To make up with Ji-woo's mom,
there's something I need to take care of.

495
00:34:43,522 --> 00:34:45,107
I'll come back after I've finished it.

496
00:34:46,233 --> 00:34:49,445
Daddy, when are you coming home?

497
00:34:52,781 --> 00:34:54,449
I'll be back as soon as I can.

498
00:34:56,994 --> 00:34:58,745
Hey. so...

499
00:34:58,746 --> 00:35:01,707
Since you're here,
can you peel some onions before you go?

500
00:35:02,875 --> 00:35:04,960
Do you have any incense left at home?

501
00:35:11,050 --> 00:35:18,057
STORE CLOSING
CLEARANCE SALE

502
00:35:20,684 --> 00:35:21,685
Boss.

503
00:35:22,478 --> 00:35:24,312
We got this new sour chicken lunch box.

504
00:35:24,313 --> 00:35:25,772
Can I try one?

505
00:35:25,773 --> 00:35:28,526
Go ahead.
There's no one else to eat it anyway.

506
00:35:30,402 --> 00:35:33,988
Were you saving it
for that police officer?

507
00:35:33,989 --> 00:35:37,368
- In that case, I won't have it.
- No, go ahead and eat.

508
00:35:38,285 --> 00:35:39,370
She won't be coming by anyway.

509
00:35:40,287 --> 00:35:42,665
Huh?
What do you mean, she won't be coming?

510
00:35:43,374 --> 00:35:44,667
Did you end things with her?

511
00:35:47,002 --> 00:35:50,089
There was nothing to end.
We were never anything to begin with.

512
00:35:52,383 --> 00:35:53,841
Just eat it so I don't have to see it.

513
00:35:53,842 --> 00:35:57,179
Yes, sir. I'll get it out of your sight.

514
00:36:06,021 --> 00:36:07,022
Mr. Gang!

515
00:36:09,191 --> 00:36:11,985
- You're early.
- I came as soon as you called.

516
00:36:11,986 --> 00:36:14,612
What's this about?
Why are you quitting all of a sudden?

517
00:36:14,613 --> 00:36:15,947
Let's talk inside.

518
00:36:15,948 --> 00:36:18,200
- Stay and eat.
- Yes, sir.

519
00:36:41,015 --> 00:36:42,016
Hold it.

520
00:36:46,562 --> 00:36:47,771
What is it?

521
00:36:48,314 --> 00:36:51,942
There's a store called 25 O'Clock
about 300 meters from here.

522
00:36:52,610 --> 00:36:54,737
- From now on, please go there instead.
- Excuse me?

523
00:37:00,909 --> 00:37:03,954
Is that what your boss said?
That I shouldn't come?

524
00:37:05,247 --> 00:37:07,166
I hate to say this, but...

525
00:37:07,291 --> 00:37:11,794
My boss lives
in a different world from you.

526
00:37:11,795 --> 00:37:15,298
He has big things ahead of him,
so don't be a distraction.

527
00:37:15,299 --> 00:37:19,844
- You should just back off now.
- Big things?

528
00:37:19,845 --> 00:37:21,137
What?

529
00:37:21,138 --> 00:37:22,890
Is he opening a supermarket or something?

530
00:37:23,641 --> 00:37:25,893
And what gives you the right
to say something like that?

531
00:37:27,686 --> 00:37:31,439
I know my boss better than anyone.

532
00:37:31,440 --> 00:37:33,108
Anyone in the world.

533
00:37:34,109 --> 00:37:38,030
Do you have any idea
how much of a nuisance you've been to him?

534
00:37:39,782 --> 00:37:40,908
Is that what he said?

535
00:37:42,951 --> 00:37:45,746
- That I was a nuisance?
- Yes, he said it himself.

536
00:37:46,372 --> 00:37:50,209
He said you were driving him crazy
when you're not even together.

537
00:37:52,461 --> 00:37:56,381
Another Friendly Convenience Store award,
and you'll get even more perks from HQ.

538
00:37:56,382 --> 00:37:59,634
- Please, think it over.
- It's just that something's come up.

539
00:37:59,635 --> 00:38:01,929
- Sorry this is so sudden.
- I don't know how to tell you this.

540
00:38:03,138 --> 00:38:04,639
But you can't close right away.

541
00:38:04,640 --> 00:38:07,935
- It'll take at least three months.
- Please do it as quickly as you can.

542
00:38:12,940 --> 00:38:13,941
Just a moment.

543
00:38:14,525 --> 00:38:15,901
I'll be taking inventory.

544
00:38:23,867 --> 00:38:27,120
- Did the headquarters...
- Jesus! Don't creep up on me!

545
00:38:27,121 --> 00:38:29,206
I've been right here the whole time.

546
00:38:30,207 --> 00:38:34,837
- No, but just now...
- Oh, the cop? She's crazy.

547
00:38:36,088 --> 00:38:37,840
- I sent her away.
- Crazy?

548
00:38:39,049 --> 00:38:40,133
You sent her away?

549
00:38:40,134 --> 00:38:42,760
Didn't you say you two were nothing?

550
00:38:42,761 --> 00:38:45,889
She keeps coming to the store,
so she's a distraction.

551
00:38:46,807 --> 00:38:49,434
So I just took care of her myself.

552
00:38:49,435 --> 00:38:51,228
What do you mean, you took care of her?

553
00:38:51,729 --> 00:38:55,065
Have you really not noticed
the way she looks at you?

554
00:38:55,607 --> 00:38:58,193
- She's into you.
- Really?

555
00:38:59,820 --> 00:39:02,614
- How would you know that?
- Hey, what do you mean, how?

556
00:39:03,741 --> 00:39:07,453
Do you have any idea how many girls
come here just to give me drinks?

557
00:39:08,412 --> 00:39:12,374
That officer had the exact same look
when she was looking at you.

558
00:39:14,293 --> 00:39:16,794
It's a good thing I nipped it in the bud.

559
00:39:16,795 --> 00:39:19,631
What would've happened
if you two had hit it off? Huh?

560
00:39:20,132 --> 00:39:22,884
Next thing you know,
you would have ended up on TV.

561
00:39:22,885 --> 00:39:27,890
The headline would read
"Collusion Between Ex-Gangster and Cop."

562
00:39:28,640 --> 00:39:30,851
Just the thought of it gives me chills.

563
00:39:32,394 --> 00:39:33,562
I did good, right?

564
00:39:35,230 --> 00:39:37,648
You're right about everything.

565
00:39:37,649 --> 00:39:38,900
Let's go with that.

566
00:39:38,901 --> 00:39:43,738
That could've been a disaster.
I really saved the day.

567
00:39:43,739 --> 00:39:45,615
HANMAEUM K-POP

568
00:39:45,616 --> 00:39:47,534
The number you have dialed
is unavailable...

569
00:39:51,830 --> 00:39:53,290
I was too harsh.

570
00:39:54,291 --> 00:39:56,668
Just tell me where you are.

571
00:40:12,768 --> 00:40:15,229
The number you are trying to reach...

572
00:40:20,692 --> 00:40:22,820
UNCLE: I WAS TOO HARSH.
JUST TELL ME WHERE YOU ARE.

573
00:40:27,783 --> 00:40:29,535
Who is it? Your uncle?

574
00:40:30,994 --> 00:40:32,078
Yeah.

575
00:40:32,079 --> 00:40:34,455
Just swallow your pride, apologize,
and go home.

576
00:40:34,456 --> 00:40:37,751
Damn it, are you crazy? I've got my pride.

577
00:40:39,545 --> 00:40:41,254
How can I just go back now?

578
00:40:41,255 --> 00:40:42,964
You're out of money for the PC cafe.

579
00:40:42,965 --> 00:40:45,050
Go home and get some money at least.

580
00:40:46,009 --> 00:40:49,136
Do you really think
I'm that much of a scumbag?

581
00:40:49,137 --> 00:40:52,390
Hey, that man is practically
living like a slave because of me.

582
00:40:52,391 --> 00:40:53,642
You want me to take his money?

583
00:40:54,601 --> 00:40:56,937
When will you grow up?

584
00:40:59,523 --> 00:41:02,776
I'll go back when I can pay him back,
plus extra, and free him.

585
00:41:03,569 --> 00:41:05,820
That's when I'll go back. In style.

586
00:41:05,821 --> 00:41:07,281
You're broke.
You think you can pull that off?

587
00:41:07,906 --> 00:41:09,448
That's why I'm trying to earn money.

588
00:41:09,449 --> 00:41:11,785
I'm scouring the part-time job sites now.

589
00:41:12,911 --> 00:41:14,329
NIGHT SHIFT, SERVERS, ENGLISH TUTOR WANTED

590
00:41:15,122 --> 00:41:18,083
Man, why is the pay so crappy
for all of these?

591
00:41:18,584 --> 00:41:19,877
Ah, damn it.

592
00:41:22,045 --> 00:41:24,171
Hey, Nam-il, I saw Jin-su yesterday.

593
00:41:24,172 --> 00:41:26,424
He said there's a gig that pays well.

594
00:41:26,425 --> 00:41:28,217
But they can't find anyone for it.

595
00:41:28,218 --> 00:41:31,304
If you're interested,
should I ask him about it for you?

596
00:41:31,305 --> 00:41:33,223
- It's not a scam, is it?
- Can't be a proper job.

597
00:41:33,724 --> 00:41:35,224
It pays a million won a day.

598
00:41:35,225 --> 00:41:38,604
What? One million won? For real?

599
00:41:46,945 --> 00:41:48,280
HEAVEN CAPITAL VICTIMS RECORD

600
00:41:52,200 --> 00:41:53,619
BONG JE-SUN / HEO NAM-IL

601
00:41:56,038 --> 00:41:57,331
Bong Je-sun.

602
00:42:01,877 --> 00:42:03,170
Yes.

603
00:42:04,671 --> 00:42:06,172
Oh, dear.

604
00:42:06,173 --> 00:42:09,009
I've prepared a nourishing meal
for you today.

605
00:42:10,469 --> 00:42:12,888
Here you go. There.

606
00:42:13,722 --> 00:42:15,098
This isn't just any regular chicken.

607
00:42:15,599 --> 00:42:19,353
It's made with a free-range chicken.
Looks delicious, right?

608
00:42:21,772 --> 00:42:22,814
Wow.

609
00:42:27,903 --> 00:42:28,987
Je-sun.

610
00:42:29,446 --> 00:42:31,280
- Yes?
- Mind if I eat with my own hands?

611
00:42:31,281 --> 00:42:32,531
- Of course.
- Okay.

612
00:42:32,532 --> 00:42:33,533
Sorry.

613
00:42:38,747 --> 00:42:39,748
Thank you.

614
00:42:40,666 --> 00:42:42,959
I'll get the bones out for you.

615
00:42:42,960 --> 00:42:45,545
Je-sun, why are you always hanging around?
Don't you have a job?

616
00:42:47,965 --> 00:42:49,256
This is my job.

617
00:42:49,257 --> 00:42:51,885
- Huh?
- Well...

618
00:42:52,970 --> 00:42:55,305
i used to have an office job,
but I got fired.

619
00:42:56,390 --> 00:43:00,685
Those thugs from Heaven Capital
came to my workplace and caused a scene.

620
00:43:00,686 --> 00:43:04,147
I see your name, Bong Je-sun,
on the victim list here.

621
00:43:04,982 --> 00:43:07,818
- Did you gamble?
- Not me. My nephew did.

622
00:43:08,485 --> 00:43:10,736
It wasn't even a large amount.
He got scammed.

623
00:43:10,737 --> 00:43:13,699
He's not even your own son.
Who takes on their nephew's debt?

624
00:43:14,908 --> 00:43:16,076
Wait.

625
00:43:16,660 --> 00:43:19,037
- Did you cosign for him?
- No, not exactly.

626
00:43:20,288 --> 00:43:23,667
It's just...
I couldn't just turn my back on him.

627
00:43:24,126 --> 00:43:28,504
Remember when I told you
I fell in the sea ten years back?

628
00:43:28,505 --> 00:43:33,343
These people came and rescued me,
and I had no memory or a place to go.

629
00:43:33,468 --> 00:43:37,180
They took me in as their son and uncle.

630
00:43:38,682 --> 00:43:41,518
So that's why you said you don't know
how you ended up in the water.

631
00:43:42,477 --> 00:43:44,354
Incredible.
It's like something out of a movie.

632
00:43:45,063 --> 00:43:48,775
- So you don't remember anything?
- It's a funny thing, right?

633
00:43:50,193 --> 00:43:53,487
I even tried hypnotherapy,
but it was no use.

634
00:43:53,488 --> 00:43:57,533
It only had me dreaming something
like a scene out of an action movie.

635
00:43:57,534 --> 00:43:58,993
- An action movie?
- Yes.

636
00:43:58,994 --> 00:44:00,037
Come in.

637
00:44:01,872 --> 00:44:04,207
Hi, Prosecutor Gang.

638
00:44:04,332 --> 00:44:07,460
I've something I need to discuss with you.
Do you have a moment?

639
00:44:07,461 --> 00:44:08,712
With me?

640
00:44:09,504 --> 00:44:12,591
You said two men followed you
when you left Seon-jung's house yesterday?

641
00:44:13,175 --> 00:44:18,388
Yes. But I'm not entirely sure.

642
00:44:19,056 --> 00:44:21,599
I'm pretty sure they were tailing me,
you know?

643
00:44:21,600 --> 00:44:23,809
So I couldn't let them follow me here.

644
00:44:23,810 --> 00:44:25,978
So I hid in an alley.
It was either me or them.

645
00:44:25,979 --> 00:44:28,356
I grabbed a wooden plank
and waited for them.

646
00:44:29,983 --> 00:44:31,401
But they just suddenly vanished.

647
00:44:31,860 --> 00:44:35,112
From the glimpse I got,
they didn't seem like regular guys.

648
00:44:35,113 --> 00:44:38,492
They looked just like the thugs
that work for Heaven Capital.

649
00:44:39,117 --> 00:44:43,829
What if they found out
we're helping the collection victims?

650
00:44:43,830 --> 00:44:45,373
What if that's why they followed me?

651
00:44:45,957 --> 00:44:48,667
But why didn't you call the police
right on the spot?

652
00:44:48,668 --> 00:44:50,044
Well, you see...

653
00:44:50,045 --> 00:44:53,339
If they're from the loan company,
it's useless to report them.

654
00:44:53,340 --> 00:44:57,635
I mean, how do you think they get away
with locking people up and beating them?

655
00:44:57,636 --> 00:44:59,387
Who do you think is backing them?

656
00:44:59,846 --> 00:45:01,889
It's no use to call the cops.

657
00:45:01,890 --> 00:45:03,350
They'd have gotten off with a warning.

658
00:45:03,975 --> 00:45:06,186
- Is it that bad?
- You don't have to look far.

659
00:45:07,104 --> 00:45:11,191
My superior, Sergeant Kim,
is a stooge for those loan sharks.

660
00:45:12,025 --> 00:45:14,401
What do we do
if it's really the Heaven Capital guys?

661
00:45:14,402 --> 00:45:16,779
I think we need to come up with a plan.

662
00:45:16,780 --> 00:45:18,948
We face them head-on. How about it?

663
00:45:18,949 --> 00:45:21,326
- Face them head-on?
- Yes. Okay.

664
00:45:22,077 --> 00:45:24,871
Could you tell me more
about this Detective Kim?

665
00:45:26,998 --> 00:45:30,043
Code One. 34 Nakwon 2-ro.
Assault reported.

666
00:45:30,168 --> 00:45:34,089
Yeah, I'm nearby. I'll take it.

667
00:45:38,051 --> 00:45:39,469
DETECTIVE KIM: DISPATCH IN 3

668
00:45:39,928 --> 00:45:41,387
Hey, stop it.

669
00:45:41,388 --> 00:45:43,514
- Let's go.
- Yes, boss.

670
00:45:43,515 --> 00:45:45,517
Everyone on Yeongseon Island knows him.

671
00:45:46,893 --> 00:45:48,477
He's supposed to be a cop.

672
00:45:48,478 --> 00:45:52,565
But instead of stopping debt collectors,
he covers for them.

673
00:45:52,566 --> 00:45:57,027
- There must be cameras around there.
- There were none.

674
00:45:57,028 --> 00:45:58,612
Are the police allowed to do this?

675
00:45:58,613 --> 00:46:01,283
How can a regular citizen
get the CCTV footage?

676
00:46:05,203 --> 00:46:08,874
As if taking bribes wasn't bad enough,
he's been corrupting his colleagues.

677
00:46:11,209 --> 00:46:14,671
There are countless loan company cases
that Detective Kim has covered up.

678
00:46:17,382 --> 00:46:19,009
At this point, he's not much of a cop.

679
00:46:20,385 --> 00:46:22,304
He's more of a goon for Heaven Capital.

680
00:46:24,222 --> 00:46:26,892
Mi-kyung, this Detective Kim.

681
00:46:27,017 --> 00:46:30,144
Remember the traffic accident
on the riverside road?

682
00:46:30,145 --> 00:46:32,689
Can you find out
if he was dispatched for it?

683
00:46:33,231 --> 00:46:34,566
How do you know about that?

684
00:46:35,400 --> 00:46:38,736
He's usually always slacking off.

685
00:46:38,737 --> 00:46:43,574
I thought it was strange
when he said he wanted to go.

686
00:46:43,575 --> 00:46:47,579
Ah, this might be easier than I thought.

687
00:46:48,205 --> 00:46:50,623
I'll go meet with Detective Kim tomorrow.

688
00:46:50,624 --> 00:46:52,083
You will?

689
00:46:54,211 --> 00:46:55,420
Recognize this place?

690
00:46:57,047 --> 00:46:59,298
Yeah, isn't this where Yoo In-gu held me?

691
00:46:59,299 --> 00:47:02,552
That's right. Yeongseon Food.
This is their base of operations.

692
00:47:03,053 --> 00:47:06,138
They package it to look like preservatives
and put it in their beef jerky.

693
00:47:06,139 --> 00:47:08,475
Then they distribute it nationwide
from Yeongseon Island.

694
00:47:08,975 --> 00:47:12,811
The day after tomorrow,
a huge drug shipment from China

695
00:47:12,812 --> 00:47:15,774
is coming into Yeongseon Island
through Yeongseon Port.

696
00:47:16,524 --> 00:47:18,235
So they're bringing it in
disguised as cargo?

697
00:47:19,069 --> 00:47:21,738
Word on the street is that the Ingu Sect
poured all their funds into this.

698
00:47:22,239 --> 00:47:26,909
We haven't confirmed that the drug money
is to go into Han Gyeong-wook's pocket.

699
00:47:26,910 --> 00:47:28,535
But still, if we stop this...

700
00:47:28,536 --> 00:47:32,290
- We can finish Yoo In-gu for good.
- Exactly.

701
00:47:33,083 --> 00:47:36,877
- You're tracking their movements, right?
- Oh, I was about to bring that up.

702
00:47:36,878 --> 00:47:40,256
Those bastards tried to go after
someone named Kim Seon-jung.

703
00:47:40,257 --> 00:47:41,382
Kim Seon-jung?

704
00:47:41,383 --> 00:47:44,219
Yes, he's Han Gyeong-wook's rival
in the mayoral election.

705
00:47:45,011 --> 00:47:47,429
He seems to have
nothing to do with the deal.

706
00:47:47,430 --> 00:47:49,265
So I'm not sure of their plan.

707
00:47:49,266 --> 00:47:52,435
Yesterday, they were even tailing a woman
who visited Kim Seon-jung's house.

708
00:47:53,019 --> 00:47:56,105
I chased them because I thought
they were about to do something.

709
00:47:56,106 --> 00:47:57,648
And I took them down.

710
00:47:57,649 --> 00:47:58,732
Did you see her face?

711
00:47:58,733 --> 00:48:02,654
Well, she got away
while I was dealing with those goons.

712
00:48:03,405 --> 00:48:05,448
But I did get her license plate.

713
00:48:06,157 --> 00:48:09,743
The Kim Seon-jung situation
doesn't seem to be related to this deal.

714
00:48:09,744 --> 00:48:11,996
So take the plate number and
look into it later.

715
00:48:11,997 --> 00:48:13,163
Okay.

716
00:48:13,164 --> 00:48:16,250
You keep tracking Yoo In-gu's movements
related to the deal.

717
00:48:16,251 --> 00:48:17,376
Got it.

718
00:48:17,377 --> 00:48:19,753
What about Prosecutor Gang?

719
00:48:19,754 --> 00:48:21,255
I know a man carried her

720
00:48:21,256 --> 00:48:23,632
and he entered the redevelopment area.

721
00:48:23,633 --> 00:48:25,342
But they've disappeared since then.

722
00:48:25,343 --> 00:48:27,428
There's no CCTV there, either.

723
00:48:27,429 --> 00:48:30,849
Damn. If only we had Prosecutor Gang,
this would be so much easier.

724
00:48:31,850 --> 00:48:34,519
- Anyway, keep looking into it.
- Okay.

725
00:48:35,687 --> 00:48:36,688
Oh, and you.

726
00:48:40,191 --> 00:48:41,484
Gang Beom-ryong.

727
00:48:44,487 --> 00:48:45,780
Gang Beom-ryong!

728
00:48:46,406 --> 00:48:49,159
- Hey.
- What? Why?

729
00:48:50,827 --> 00:48:53,496
- What?
- What do you think?

730
00:48:55,248 --> 00:48:56,499
About what?

731
00:48:57,208 --> 00:48:59,919
Don't you have any idea
what Yoo In-gu's next move will be?

732
00:49:01,004 --> 00:49:05,050
He used to work for you.
You must know him better than anyone.

733
00:49:06,968 --> 00:49:08,470
Right.

734
00:49:10,138 --> 00:49:13,391
Why do you need my opinion?
Gong-bok already did all the research.

735
00:49:15,769 --> 00:49:17,145
Were you even listening?

736
00:49:18,396 --> 00:49:19,480
Give me a break.

737
00:49:19,481 --> 00:49:21,858
I only missed a bit
because I was thinking.

738
00:49:22,859 --> 00:49:24,527
Come on, I got the gist of it.

739
00:49:26,654 --> 00:49:30,700
We're on the verge of drugs flooding
Yeongseon Island, and you're zoning out?

740
00:49:31,409 --> 00:49:33,077
I wouldn't expect any less
from an ex-thug.

741
00:49:33,078 --> 00:49:35,537
No sense of responsibility, no passion.

742
00:49:35,538 --> 00:49:39,000
This guy, I swear.
It's always about me being a gangster.

743
00:49:39,501 --> 00:49:42,337
Hey, you think gangsters
don't have feelings?

744
00:49:43,046 --> 00:49:44,672
Ever think about a gangster's feelings?

745
00:49:46,508 --> 00:49:49,344
What? Why the hell are you getting mad?

746
00:49:50,637 --> 00:49:52,221
- Don't stop me.
- Hands off!

747
00:49:52,222 --> 00:49:53,223
I wasn't touching you.

748
00:49:57,894 --> 00:49:59,104
Hey, what's gotten into you?

749
00:50:03,650 --> 00:50:05,526
Look, I got the gist of it.

750
00:50:05,527 --> 00:50:08,862
So if you need anything from me,
just tell Gong-bok.

751
00:50:08,863 --> 00:50:11,324
I've got things to do at the store,
so I'm off.

752
00:50:16,037 --> 00:50:19,499
- Beom-ryong!
- What was that about?

753
00:50:21,543 --> 00:50:22,544
Beom-ryong.

754
00:50:23,503 --> 00:50:24,546
Get home safe.

755
00:50:25,922 --> 00:50:29,925
- I'm sorry. I got a little carried away.
- Nothing to be sorry about.

756
00:50:29,926 --> 00:50:31,052
Still...

757
00:50:32,053 --> 00:50:34,305
You seem really stressed out.

758
00:50:37,225 --> 00:50:39,351
So that's why he's acting like this?

759
00:50:39,352 --> 00:50:41,937
Because of that cop he had a crush on?

760
00:50:41,938 --> 00:50:44,898
Yes, he said nothing's
going on between them.

761
00:50:44,899 --> 00:50:46,901
But ever since her visit,
he's been like that.

762
00:50:49,070 --> 00:50:50,487
That's not good.

763
00:50:50,488 --> 00:50:53,283
- Why's that?
- We're moving in tomorrow.

764
00:50:54,200 --> 00:50:55,701
He could sabotage the whole thing.

765
00:50:55,702 --> 00:50:59,204
Come on, Beom-ryong was a legend
in the Hwasan Sect.

766
00:50:59,205 --> 00:51:02,167
You think he'd mess up a job
over some trouble with a girl?

767
00:51:02,292 --> 00:51:06,880
So you're sure Gang Beom-ryong
will be over that woman by tomorrow?

768
00:51:07,881 --> 00:51:11,217
Do you think your boss is
that rational and level-headed?

769
00:51:11,759 --> 00:51:12,927
No, not at all.

770
00:51:15,346 --> 00:51:18,975
Tell me everything you know
about Gang Beom-ryong.

771
00:51:26,399 --> 00:51:28,276
Hey, Mi-kyung. Get over here.

772
00:51:30,195 --> 00:51:31,613
Hurry up and get over here.

773
00:51:33,907 --> 00:51:37,494
Why do you keep sticking your nose
where it doesn't belong?

774
00:51:37,619 --> 00:51:40,621
You think all cops are the same?
There are ranks, you know.

775
00:51:40,622 --> 00:51:43,332
You barely got that ID around your neck
at your age.

776
00:51:43,333 --> 00:51:45,626
You should learn to stay in your lane.

777
00:51:45,627 --> 00:51:49,130
Ugh, this is so frustrating.
How'd you even get in?

778
00:51:50,298 --> 00:51:52,300
Get your shit together.

779
00:52:04,395 --> 00:52:06,064
- Turning yourself in?
- Jesus!

780
00:52:07,774 --> 00:52:10,275
Hey, what's your deal?

781
00:52:10,276 --> 00:52:11,903
How did you know I'd be here?

782
00:52:13,196 --> 00:52:15,281
You look right at home.

783
00:52:15,740 --> 00:52:17,157
- What?
- Yeah.

784
00:52:17,158 --> 00:52:20,285
Turning yourself in wouldn't be
that terrible of an idea.

785
00:52:20,286 --> 00:52:22,288
It's one way to repent
for all that you've done.

786
00:52:23,790 --> 00:52:24,916
But that's not it, is it?

787
00:52:25,583 --> 00:52:27,794
Why are you staring at the station
so wistfully?

788
00:52:28,878 --> 00:52:30,964
It's because of that cop from earlier,
isn't it?

789
00:52:32,090 --> 00:52:35,593
- Who?
- She's way out of your league.

790
00:52:35,718 --> 00:52:37,469
Don't you think
you're in two different films?

791
00:52:37,470 --> 00:52:41,265
She's romance, you're crime thriller.
You don't match at all.

792
00:52:41,266 --> 00:52:43,850
If you ask me,
a store owner and a regular.

793
00:52:43,851 --> 00:52:45,562
Thta's the best you can hope for.

794
00:52:46,896 --> 00:52:48,273
- Did Gong-bok talk again?
- Yep.

795
00:52:49,482 --> 00:52:50,566
Leave me alone.

796
00:52:50,567 --> 00:52:52,277
It's not what you
and Gong-bok are worried about.

797
00:52:52,735 --> 00:52:55,780
- I didn't come this way over Mi-kyung.
- Then what?

798
00:52:56,447 --> 00:52:58,199
Why are you here at such a critical time?

799
00:52:59,701 --> 00:53:00,868
Gang Beom-ryong.

800
00:53:01,411 --> 00:53:03,704
- Don't you know what's important?
- I know.

801
00:53:03,705 --> 00:53:05,163
What do you know?

802
00:53:05,164 --> 00:53:09,210
- I want to end this so badly!
- I packed a bag and left my home!

803
00:53:14,340 --> 00:53:17,593
Tomorrow's operation will be hard
even if we're at our 100%.

804
00:53:17,594 --> 00:53:20,345
If you juggle everything at once,
you'll end up dropping it all.

805
00:53:20,346 --> 00:53:22,264
Whether it's Yoo In-gu or Han Gyeong-wook

806
00:53:22,265 --> 00:53:25,351
we gotta finish this so you can go back
to the life you want, right?

807
00:53:26,269 --> 00:53:28,479
So stop getting distracted
and focus on the task.

808
00:53:29,188 --> 00:53:32,775
Asking her out and getting turned down
can wait until the job is done.

809
00:53:34,527 --> 00:53:36,321
I know that.
Don't act like you know everything.

810
00:53:37,280 --> 00:53:40,408
Once this is all over,
I'll go and talk to her for real!

811
00:53:42,869 --> 00:53:47,080
But the way I see it,
I don't think you have a shot.

812
00:53:47,081 --> 00:53:51,001
That's ridiculous.
Gong-bok said Mi-kyung is into me too.

813
00:53:51,002 --> 00:53:53,670
You believe that?
I bet he was just being nice.

814
00:53:53,671 --> 00:53:55,672
Does he look like he cares about me?

815
00:53:55,673 --> 00:53:58,760
But still.
What will you do if she turns you down?

816
00:54:02,930 --> 00:54:05,849
What, is this it? There's nothing.

817
00:54:05,850 --> 00:54:09,645
Sir, Kkot-nim and I have been
watching him like a hawk.

818
00:54:09,646 --> 00:54:13,691
But not a single soul came near the place.
He's very meticulous.

819
00:54:15,610 --> 00:54:19,029
- Did you tail him?
- Just his office and his regular diner.

820
00:54:19,030 --> 00:54:21,407
- He meets no one privately.
- Screw it.

821
00:54:22,283 --> 00:54:25,995
We'd never find any dirt on him
even if we looked for months.

822
00:54:26,120 --> 00:54:29,457
If a guy is this clean,
even Chairman Do won't find anything.

823
00:54:30,083 --> 00:54:33,086
It is a shame
I couldn't outdo him this time, though.

824
00:54:34,128 --> 00:54:37,882
I'll settle for sitting back
and watching him get an earful.

825
00:54:38,549 --> 00:54:42,762
Let's drop this and focus on our deal.
You know what I mean?

826
00:54:43,596 --> 00:54:44,597
Yes, sir.

827
00:54:48,601 --> 00:54:52,271
Besides that woman, no one else has been
in or out of Kim Seon-jung's house.

828
00:54:52,397 --> 00:54:56,109
- Did you ID this woman?
- She's definitely no ordinary woman.

829
00:54:56,776 --> 00:55:01,197
Just as we were about to grab her,
some guy appeared.

830
00:55:01,989 --> 00:55:03,783
He totally ambushed us.

831
00:55:04,951 --> 00:55:07,786
It's obvious she has someone
watching her back.

832
00:55:07,787 --> 00:55:10,872
- Watching her back?
- But take a look here.

833
00:55:10,873 --> 00:55:12,959
- Right.
- Yes, right there.

834
00:55:13,418 --> 00:55:14,460
I got a picture of the plate.

835
00:55:17,755 --> 00:55:20,591
And you're sure Yoo knows
nothing about this woman?

836
00:55:20,717 --> 00:55:22,218
Oh, yes. I haven't told him a thing.

837
00:55:23,010 --> 00:55:26,596
So for now, he's going to
stop worrying about Kim Seon-jung

838
00:55:26,597 --> 00:55:28,224
and focus on the deal.

839
00:55:29,851 --> 00:55:30,935
Okay, okay.

840
00:55:31,686 --> 00:55:34,480
Let's make sure we keep it that way.

841
00:55:34,605 --> 00:55:37,190
Don't let him get distracted
by pointless things. Okay?

842
00:55:37,191 --> 00:55:38,275
Yes, sir.

843
00:55:38,276 --> 00:55:41,027
You can go.
You must be busy with the upcoming deal.

844
00:55:41,028 --> 00:55:42,029
Yes, sir.

845
00:55:49,495 --> 00:55:52,205
Kim Seon-jung...

846
00:55:52,206 --> 00:55:53,790
Seems like there's a new variable.

847
00:55:53,791 --> 00:55:55,793
Should we revise the Kim Seon-jung plan?

848
00:55:56,252 --> 00:55:57,377
No, no.

849
00:55:57,378 --> 00:55:59,755
For now, let's stick with our plan.

850
00:55:59,756 --> 00:56:02,507
No point in flipping a table
that's already set.

851
00:56:02,508 --> 00:56:04,801
Then I'll proceed as planned.

852
00:56:04,802 --> 00:56:07,221
Wait. It can't hurt to be cautious.

853
00:56:08,222 --> 00:56:11,308
Run this woman's plate
and find out who she is.

854
00:56:11,309 --> 00:56:12,643
You said she's no ordinary woman.

855
00:56:13,269 --> 00:56:16,688
We need to see if she'll affect our plan.

856
00:56:16,689 --> 00:56:19,901
- We should at least check.
- Yes, understood.

857
00:56:27,283 --> 00:56:30,244
Man, the flame is too low.

858
00:56:35,708 --> 00:56:37,668
Why is this so tough?

859
00:56:38,461 --> 00:56:42,380
This's cheap beef.
Are you passing it off as prime grade?

860
00:56:42,381 --> 00:56:44,257
Please, just go.

861
00:56:44,258 --> 00:56:47,302
You're disturbing my business
when you're eating for free.

862
00:56:47,303 --> 00:56:49,304
Don't go making false accusations.

863
00:56:49,305 --> 00:56:50,515
When did I disturb your business?

864
00:56:51,390 --> 00:56:54,017
I mean, this is just awful.

865
00:56:54,018 --> 00:56:55,268
So tough.

866
00:56:55,269 --> 00:56:57,063
The meat here is tough!

867
00:56:57,688 --> 00:57:00,774
Here's your money, so please.

868
00:57:00,775 --> 00:57:02,567
Please, just go. Okay?

869
00:57:02,568 --> 00:57:05,029
See, was that so hard?

870
00:57:05,404 --> 00:57:07,781
Why'd you have to make things difficult?

871
00:57:07,782 --> 00:57:08,991
You're a cop.

872
00:57:09,700 --> 00:57:10,868
Don't you know this is wrong?

873
00:57:11,452 --> 00:57:12,869
But it's not.

874
00:57:12,870 --> 00:57:14,037
Look, lady.

875
00:57:14,038 --> 00:57:17,250
Don't you see those shops getting
shut down by Heaven Capital?

876
00:57:17,375 --> 00:57:20,378
And who's letting you stay in business?
It's all thanks to me.

877
00:57:20,920 --> 00:57:22,755
What's the point of me working all day?

878
00:57:23,339 --> 00:57:27,301
If you keep taking all my money,
how am I supposed to survive?

879
00:57:28,052 --> 00:57:29,053
Lady.

880
00:57:29,846 --> 00:57:32,347
You should just work harder.

881
00:57:32,348 --> 00:57:33,808
I believe in you!

882
00:57:34,433 --> 00:57:36,852
Stop annoying me
and get me some beef to go.

883
00:57:36,853 --> 00:57:38,395
For my family.

884
00:57:38,396 --> 00:57:39,772
Hurry, hurry, hurry.

885
00:57:50,992 --> 00:57:52,075
What the hell?

886
00:57:52,076 --> 00:57:53,411
What are you doing here?

887
00:57:54,078 --> 00:57:55,413
I'm on patrol.

888
00:57:55,705 --> 00:57:56,747
Patrol?

889
00:57:58,207 --> 00:57:59,208
What patrol?

890
00:58:06,924 --> 00:58:08,467
Looking for thugs like you.

891
00:58:10,720 --> 00:58:13,013
What? Park Mi-kyung,
are you out of your mind?

892
00:58:13,014 --> 00:58:15,974
You're the one who's out of your mind.
Not Officer Park.

893
00:58:15,975 --> 00:58:18,311
- What? Who are you?
- I'm so disappointed.

894
00:58:19,312 --> 00:58:21,730
I thought you were
desperately looking for me.

895
00:58:21,731 --> 00:58:22,982
You don't even recognize me?

896
00:58:24,400 --> 00:58:26,651
What are you saying? Who are you?

897
00:58:26,652 --> 00:58:27,736
Me?

898
00:58:27,737 --> 00:58:29,446
Well, Sergeant Kim.

899
00:58:29,447 --> 00:58:32,241
I'm the one you're dying to find
in Yeongseon River.

900
00:58:33,117 --> 00:58:34,368
Prosecutor Gang Yeong-ae.

901
00:58:35,578 --> 00:58:38,372
What? Don't be ridiculous.

902
00:58:39,123 --> 00:58:40,458
You went to great lengths.

903
00:58:41,167 --> 00:58:45,545
To make it look like a simple accident.

904
00:58:45,546 --> 00:58:47,881
Once you've served your time
for destroying evidence, you'll know.

905
00:58:47,882 --> 00:58:49,592
Whether I'm just a ghost...

906
00:58:50,509 --> 00:58:51,928
or Gang Yeong-ae.

907
00:58:58,225 --> 00:59:00,227
- What are you doing here?
- I was just worried.

908
00:59:19,664 --> 00:59:20,665
Are you okay?

909
00:59:35,262 --> 00:59:36,305
Are you okay?

910
00:59:51,529 --> 00:59:53,030
MY CASH COW 2

911
00:59:55,574 --> 00:59:57,534
Pick up your damn phone, will you?

912
00:59:57,535 --> 01:00:00,203
Sorry, I was in the middle of something.

913
01:00:00,204 --> 01:00:02,038
What's going on, boss?

914
01:00:02,039 --> 01:00:04,666
What do you think?
The shipment from China is tomorrow.

915
01:00:04,667 --> 01:00:09,088
- Didn't I tell you to prepare?
- Oh, yes. I remember.

916
01:00:11,465 --> 01:00:15,761
Anyway, make sure no cops
are sniffing around Yeongseon Port.

917
01:00:16,345 --> 01:00:19,347
And check for suspicious people
like that Martial Arts Master.

918
01:00:19,348 --> 01:00:20,765
Make sure to make your rounds.

919
01:00:20,766 --> 01:00:22,810
- Yes, of course, sir.
- Okay.

920
01:00:25,438 --> 01:00:26,439
Sergeant Kim.

921
01:00:28,524 --> 01:00:30,735
Looks like we have a lot to talk about.

922
01:00:35,489 --> 01:00:36,532
Mr. Bong.

923
01:00:37,241 --> 01:00:38,617
- Yes?
- Can you get up now?

924
01:00:39,118 --> 01:00:40,327
Yes, I'm good.

925
01:00:46,459 --> 01:00:48,044
Just a...

926
01:00:52,131 --> 01:00:54,632
Jang Yeong-gi,
Nampo Police, Narcotics Unit 2.

927
01:00:54,633 --> 01:00:55,801
Guess who?

928
01:00:58,721 --> 01:01:01,057
Why'd you call here?
You should've just called my cell.

929
01:01:01,182 --> 01:01:02,932
You're no fun.

930
01:01:02,933 --> 01:01:04,809
Never mind. I'll explain later.

931
01:01:04,810 --> 01:01:06,686
Yeong-gi.

932
01:01:06,687 --> 01:01:10,231
- Want to make a big bust?
- Why? What's up?

933
01:01:10,232 --> 01:01:12,109
Something really big just came up.

934
01:01:12,568 --> 01:01:14,736
I'm on Yeongseon Island.
Come over here tomorrow.

935
01:01:14,737 --> 01:01:16,446
It's been a while
since we worked together.

936
01:01:16,447 --> 01:01:17,530
Boss.

937
01:01:17,531 --> 01:01:19,949
You quit being a cop
and worked so hard to get that job.

938
01:01:19,950 --> 01:01:21,951
You should be doing desk work.

939
01:01:21,952 --> 01:01:24,245
Why are you still
running around the field?

940
01:01:24,246 --> 01:01:27,083
Hey, since when have you been so stuck up?

941
01:01:28,459 --> 01:01:30,001
Is that how I taught you?

942
01:01:30,002 --> 01:01:31,962
I'm just worried about you.

943
01:01:33,214 --> 01:01:34,423
Fine, what is it?

944
01:01:36,801 --> 01:01:39,260
- Hey, thanks for lending me your phone.
- Oh, sure.

945
01:01:39,261 --> 01:01:40,637
Did the call go well?

946
01:01:40,638 --> 01:01:41,972
Detectives will be here tomorrow.

947
01:01:45,601 --> 01:01:47,310
- Are you feeling okay?
- I will be.

948
01:01:47,311 --> 01:01:48,729
I'm still a little tingly, though.

949
01:01:58,531 --> 01:02:00,532
I think I have to get back now.

950
01:02:00,533 --> 01:02:02,951
What should I do with him?
Should I just lock him up?

951
01:02:02,952 --> 01:02:05,663
You can't lock me up! I'm innocent!

952
01:02:08,415 --> 01:02:11,252
No. Let's bring him with us for now.

953
01:02:15,631 --> 01:02:17,590
Those Ingu Sect bastards.

954
01:02:17,591 --> 01:02:19,760
I thought it was strange
how quiet they've been.

955
01:02:21,303 --> 01:02:24,305
I think they're using high school kids
from Yeongseon as human shields.

956
01:02:24,306 --> 01:02:27,184
Using high schoolers in a drug deal?
That's insane.

957
01:02:27,309 --> 01:02:29,894
Exactly. Even gangs usually have rules.

958
01:02:29,895 --> 01:02:32,897
Geum Kang-sik alone has met
with 20 to 30 high school students.

959
01:02:32,898 --> 01:02:35,024
They think it's just a high-paying job.

960
01:02:35,025 --> 01:02:37,236
It'll get complicated
with too many people.

961
01:02:37,778 --> 01:02:40,447
And we can't just mess with
these kids who know nothing.

962
01:02:42,867 --> 01:02:45,536
We'll find a way.

963
01:02:50,833 --> 01:02:52,250
This is a guy named Baek.

964
01:02:52,251 --> 01:02:54,378
A specialist in smuggling
and illegal immigration.

965
01:02:55,087 --> 01:02:59,425
He bribed officials at Yeongseon Port
and set up an office for his smuggling op.

966
01:02:59,717 --> 01:03:02,219
No one smuggles anything into
or out of Yeongseon without him.

967
01:03:03,012 --> 01:03:05,847
Same with Yoo In-gu's drugs tomorrow.

968
01:03:05,848 --> 01:03:07,807
Baek is the one accommodating it.

969
01:03:07,808 --> 01:03:11,477
We just have to secure the location
and set it up perfectly.

970
01:03:11,478 --> 01:03:13,147
we definitely have a fighting chance.

971
01:03:14,231 --> 01:03:16,150
Is that even possible?

972
01:03:17,151 --> 01:03:18,359
What's our objective?

973
01:03:18,360 --> 01:03:22,614
Even if we report the drugs,
Yoo and Han will obviously find a way out.

974
01:03:22,615 --> 01:03:25,325
And it's not like
we can take down all their men.

975
01:03:25,326 --> 01:03:27,536
But if we're just trying
to screw Yoo In-gu over?

976
01:03:28,162 --> 01:03:31,332
If that's our only objective,
then it's not impossible.

977
01:03:34,335 --> 01:03:37,962
I'm starting to see the picture.
So, what should we do first?

978
01:03:37,963 --> 01:03:40,799
- You and Gong-bok can set up the stage.
- With Gong-bok?

979
01:03:43,177 --> 01:03:46,054
- You think a civilian can pull it off?
- Hey, I can do anything.

980
01:03:46,055 --> 01:03:47,056
Just you watch.

981
01:03:52,144 --> 01:03:53,437
Okay, so what about me?

982
01:03:54,521 --> 01:03:56,690
- Should I be on standby?
- You're with me.

983
01:03:57,399 --> 01:03:58,609
We're securing the location.

984
01:04:00,945 --> 01:04:03,780
- Not confident going alone?
- I could go by myself.

985
01:04:03,781 --> 01:04:06,991
I just thought
I'd give you something to do.

986
01:04:06,992 --> 01:04:08,285
So shut up and follow my lead.

987
01:04:09,620 --> 01:04:11,622
- Fine. When are we going?
- Now.

988
01:04:12,915 --> 01:04:14,208
Hey, Kim.

989
01:04:15,626 --> 01:04:16,876
Geez.

990
01:04:16,877 --> 01:04:18,545
Is this your first day in business?

991
01:04:19,964 --> 01:04:23,717
The goods will be transported safely.

992
01:04:23,842 --> 01:04:26,387
- Don't worry. Just buy me a drink.
- Hey, boys!

993
01:04:28,722 --> 01:04:29,848
Wait, hold on.

994
01:04:30,474 --> 01:04:32,517
- What the hell?
- I don't have much time.

995
01:04:32,518 --> 01:04:34,435
So I'll keep it short.

996
01:04:34,436 --> 01:04:37,981
There's an important shipment coming in
from China tomorrow night, right?

997
01:04:37,982 --> 01:04:40,651
We need to make some adjustments
to those goods.

998
01:04:40,943 --> 01:04:44,113
So, we need to borrow your little shop
for just two days.

999
01:04:44,613 --> 01:04:48,616
Think of it as a location sponsorship.

1000
01:04:48,617 --> 01:04:50,076
What the hell?

1001
01:04:50,077 --> 01:04:53,746
What are these assholes on about?

1002
01:04:53,747 --> 01:04:56,041
Hey, what are you doing? Get 'em!

1003
01:05:02,256 --> 01:05:04,007
What are you waiting for? Get out.

1004
01:05:04,008 --> 01:05:05,843
- By myself? What about you?
- You scared?

1005
01:05:06,635 --> 01:05:08,095
Scared? Hell no.

1006
01:05:13,350 --> 01:05:15,978
SPECIAL THANKS TO
KIM SANG-KYUNG AND KWON YUL

1007
01:05:30,701 --> 01:05:33,703
Location secured. Now let's get set up.

1008
01:05:33,704 --> 01:05:34,872
Now we're real allies.

1009
01:05:36,832 --> 01:05:38,916
- Aren't you worried?
- My calculations are never off.

1010
01:05:38,917 --> 01:05:42,003
Something was definitely
going on between them.

1011
01:05:42,004 --> 01:05:44,005
- All by yourself?
- Want to come with me then?

1012
01:05:44,006 --> 01:05:46,467
- I'll do whatever.
- Be honest. Did something happen?

1013
01:05:46,592 --> 01:05:48,426
- I'm pregnant.
- Pregnant?

1014
01:05:48,427 --> 01:05:50,720
- You believe that crap?
- Shut up.

1015
01:05:50,721 --> 01:05:53,598
I know better than anyone
just how evil Han Gyeong-wook is.

1016
01:05:53,599 --> 01:05:55,600
The package is delivered.

1017
01:05:55,601 --> 01:05:58,270
If we're going to set it off,
it might as well be a good show.

1018
01:05:59,229 --> 01:06:01,439
I have to save him.
He could die if he stays there.

1019
01:06:01,440 --> 01:06:04,233
- Hey, boss!
- I was wondering when you'd show up.

1020
01:06:04,234 --> 01:06:05,527
It was you?
